1. Overview

   This module removes SIP headers from incoming messages unless they are
   part of the module whitelist.

   Headers required by RFC 3261 (Via, To, From, CSeq, Call-ID) are always
   kept. Additional groups of headers can be enabled or disabled through
   module parameters.

   Custom header names can be whitelisted with the keep_header parameter.

2. Dependencies

   2.1. Kamailio Modules
   2.2. External Libraries or Applications

2.1. Kamailio Modules

   The following modules must be loaded before this module:
     * None.

2.2. External Libraries or Applications

   The following libraries or applications must be installed before
   running Kamailio with this module loaded:
     * None.

3. Parameters

   3.1. keep_described_rfc3261 (int)
   3.2. keep_path_rfc3327 (int)
   3.3. keep_diversion_rfc5806 (int)
   3.4. keep_rpid (int)
   3.5. keep_refer_to_rfc3515 (int)
   3.6. keep_sipifmatch_rfc3903 (int)
   3.7. keep_session_expires_rfc4028 (int)
   3.8. keep_min_se_rfc4028 (int)
   3.9. keep_accept_contact_rfc3841 (int)
   3.10. keep_allow_events_rfc3265 (int)
   3.11. keep_referred_by_rfc3892 (int)
   3.12. keep_reject_contact_rfc3841 (int)
   3.13. keep_request_disposition_rfc3841 (int)
   3.14. keep_identity_rfc4474 (int)
   3.15. keep_identity_info_rfc4474 (int)
   3.16. keep_ppi_rfc3325 (int)
   3.17. keep_pai_rfc3325 (int)
   3.18. keep_privacy_rfc3323 (int)
