   3.20. keep_header (string)
   3.21. keep_header_case_sensitive (int)
   3.22. params_json_file (string)

3.1. keep_described_rfc3261 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of headers described (but not required) by
   RFC 3261, for example Contact, Max-Forwards, Route, Record-Route,
   Content-*, Authorization and related headers.

   If this parameter is set to 0, specific headers can still be kept with
   keep_header.

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.1. Set keep_described_rfc3261 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_described_rfc3261", 1)
...

3.2. keep_path_rfc3327 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Path header (RFC 3327).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.2. Set keep_path_rfc3327 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_path_rfc3327", 1)
...

3.3. keep_diversion_rfc5806 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Diversion header (RFC 5806).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.3. Set keep_diversion_rfc5806 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_diversion_rfc5806", 1)
...

3.4. keep_rpid (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Remote-Party-ID header.

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.4. Set keep_rpid parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_rpid", 1)
...

3.5. keep_refer_to_rfc3515 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Refer-To header (RFC 3515).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.5. Set keep_refer_to_rfc3515 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_refer_to_rfc3515", 1)
...

3.6. keep_sipifmatch_rfc3903 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of SIP-If-Match header (RFC 3903).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.6. Set keep_sipifmatch_rfc3903 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_sipifmatch_rfc3903", 1)
...

3.7. keep_session_expires_rfc4028 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Session-Expires header (RFC 4028).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.7. Set keep_session_expires_rfc4028 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_session_expires_rfc4028", 1)
...

3.8. keep_min_se_rfc4028 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Min-SE header (RFC 4028).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.8. Set keep_min_se_rfc4028 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_min_se_rfc4028", 1)
...

3.9. keep_accept_contact_rfc3841 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Accept-Contact header (RFC 3841).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.9. Set keep_accept_contact_rfc3841 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_accept_contact_rfc3841", 1)
...

3.10. keep_allow_events_rfc3265 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Allow-Events header (RFC 3265).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.10. Set keep_allow_events_rfc3265 parameter
...
