...

3.11. keep_referred_by_rfc3892 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Referred-By header (RFC 3892).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.11. Set keep_referred_by_rfc3892 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_referred_by_rfc3892", 1)
...

3.12. keep_reject_contact_rfc3841 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Reject-Contact header (RFC 3841).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.12. Set keep_reject_contact_rfc3841 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_reject_contact_rfc3841", 1)
...

3.13. keep_request_disposition_rfc3841 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Request-Disposition header (RFC 3841).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.13. Set keep_request_disposition_rfc3841 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_request_disposition_rfc3841", 1)
...

3.14. keep_identity_rfc4474 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Identity header (RFC 4474).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.14. Set keep_identity_rfc4474 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_identity_rfc4474", 1)
...

3.15. keep_identity_info_rfc4474 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Identity-Info header (RFC 4474).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.15. Set keep_identity_info_rfc4474 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_identity_info_rfc4474", 1)
...

3.16. keep_ppi_rfc3325 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of P-Preferred-Identity header (RFC 3325).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.16. Set keep_ppi_rfc3325 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_ppi_rfc3325", 1)
...

3.17. keep_pai_rfc3325 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of P-Asserted-Identity header (RFC 3325).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.17. Set keep_pai_rfc3325 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_pai_rfc3325", 1)
...

3.18. keep_privacy_rfc3323 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Privacy header (RFC 3323).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.18. Set keep_privacy_rfc3323 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_privacy_rfc3323", 1)
...

3.19. keep_reason_rfc3326 (int)

   Enable or disable keeping of Reason header (RFC 3326).

   Default value is 1 (enabled).

   Example 1.19. Set keep_reason_rfc3326 parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_reason_rfc3326", 1)
...

3.20. keep_header (string)

   Additional header names to keep. The value is parsed as a
   semicolon-separated list of names (for example, “X-Foo;X-Bar”).

   This parameter can be set multiple times; values are accumulated.

   Default value is empty.

   Example 1.20. Set keep_header parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_header", "X-Foo;X-Bar")
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_header", "Contact")
...

3.21. keep_header_case_sensitive (int)

   Controls case sensitivity when matching header names from keep_header
   against SIP headers.

   Value “1” enables case-sensitive matching; value “0” enables
   case-insensitive matching.

   When JSON profiles are used, this value is applied per profile from
   each profile object.

   Default value is 1 (case-sensitive).

   Example 1.21. Set keep_header_case_sensitive parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_header_case_sensitive", 0)
...

3.22. params_json_file (string)

   Path to a JSON file containing an array of profile objects. Each object
   must define profile_name.

   Unnamed profile objects are skipped and a warning is logged:
   “profile[id] without name will be skipped due to unnamed”.

   If this parameter is not set, an internal default profile named
   “default” is created from module parameters.

   If this parameter is set and script function whitelist_headers() is
   used (without explicit profile), the first profile from the loaded
   array (index 0) is used.

   Example 1.22. Set params_json_file parameter
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "params_json_file",
    "/etc/kamailio/headers_whitelist_profiles.json")
...

   Example 1.23. JSON profiles file structure
...
[
    {
        "profile_name": "edge_inbound",
        "keep_header_case_sensitive": 0,
        "keep_header": [
            "X-Trace-ID",
            "X-Request-ID",
            "P-Charging-Vector"
        ]
    },
    {
        "profile_name": "trunk_minimal",
        "keep_described_rfc3261": 0,
        "keep_path_rfc3327": 0,
        "keep_diversion_rfc5806": 0,
        "keep_rpid": 0,
        "keep_reason_rfc3326": 0,
        "keep_header_case_sensitive": 1,
        "keep_header": [
            "X-Custom-Trunk"
        ]
    }
]
...

4. Functions

   4.1. whitelist_headers()
   4.2. whitelist_headers_with_profile(profile)

4.1.  whitelist_headers()

   Removes all SIP headers except the ones allowed by RFC 3261 and enabled
   by module parameters.

   The function marks headers for deletion using lumps. In normal
   request/reply routing, changes are applied automatically.

   To force immediate effect during configuration processing, call
   msg_apply_changes() afterwards.

   It can be used in REQUEST_ROUTE, ONREPLY_ROUTE, FAILURE_ROUTE, and
   BRANCH_ROUTE.

   When JSON profiles are enabled via params_json_file, this function logs
   a warning and applies the first profile from loaded profile array
   (index 0).

   Example 1.24. whitelist_headers usage
...
whitelist_headers();
...

4.2.  whitelist_headers_with_profile(profile)

   Same behavior as whitelist_headers(), but uses a specific whitelist
   profile by name.

   The profile must exist in loaded profiles (from JSON or default
   profile).

   Example 1.25. whitelist_headers_with_profile usage
...
whitelist_headers_with_profile("default");
...

5. RPC Commands

   5.1. hwl.reload
   5.2. hwl.profiles_list

5.1. hwl.reload

   Reload module profiles and parameters from current module
   configuration.

5.2. hwl.profiles_list

   List loaded profiles. Returned fields include profile_name, profile_id,
   all keep_* profile flags, and keep_header array.

6. Examples

   See files: doc/examples/headers_whitelist_example.cfg and
   doc/examples/headers_whitelist_profiles.json.

7. Event Routes

   This module does not export event routes.
